What will be covered

Joe asked to answer the following:

  • What were your project GOALS?
  • What did you DO?
  • What did you LEARN?

I would also like to tell you about:

  • What we did NOT DO
  • Why not
  • What is yet to be done

What were your project GOALS?

  • 1. to flip introductory graduate statistics course that introduces R programming
  • 2. to produce a set of interactive lessons using swirl

What we DID

  • flipped introductory graduate statistics course base on R
    Specifically,
  • course portal/calendar and log
  • video lectures, radio podcasts, slides, scripts, etc.
  • course specific materials such as lectures, timeline, demonstrations (see ./materials)

What else we DID

  • sourced bibliography and content scope of the course
  • review of online resources on statistics with R
  • reproducible examples of real-life analytic reporting
  • publishing self-containt github repository with all course materials

What did we NOT DO?

  • we did not produce a set of interactive lessons using swirl. We hoped to to extend the existing collection of swirl courses, but flipping the course consumed of our resources.

so before telling you we should get the money to do it after all, let me tell you about

Student Reviews

  • some felt overwhelmed with R
  • desired less focus on programming
  • many wanted more structure beyond the readings and videos
  • loved self-paced videos
  • appreciated documented examples

Next Steps
